questions.question_text_1: Consider a client which is located 3000 km from the server makes a request through the cable. Suddenly after the request reaches the server, the cable breaks and the response is now to be sent to the client via air. This change of medium caused an additional delay of 30 ms at the server end. How long will the client have to wait for receiving the response? (speed on cable = 2e8 m/s and in air 3e8 m/s)
